# Amazon EKS Complete Setup Guide

## Step 1: Login to AWS Console

## Step 2: Create IAM Role for EKS Control Plane
    Navigate to: IAM → Roles → Create Role

Details

## Step 3: Create VPC (If Not Available)

VPC
subnet
Internet Gateway
Route Tables


## Step 4: Create EKS Cluster

Go to: EKS → Clusters → Create Cluster

| Parameter          | Value                         |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------- |
| Name               | my-eks-cluster                |
| Kubernetes Version | Latest Supported              |
| Cluster IAM Role   | eks-cluster-role              |
| VPC                | Select VPC                    |
| Subnets            | Select Private/Public Subnets |
| Security Group     | Existing or New               |


Cluster creation takes approximately: 10-15 minutes

## Step 5: Create Node Group

After cluster becomes Active: Cluster → Compute → Add Node Group

Create Node IAM Role : eks-node-role = HOW

Attach:
    AmazonEKSWorkerNodePolicy
    AmazonEC2ContainerRegistryReadOnly
    AmazonEKS_CNI_Policy

Node Group Settings:

| Parameter | Example   |
| --------- | --------- |
| Name      | worker-ng |
| Instance  | m6a.large |
| Min       | 1         |
| Desired   | 2         |
| Max       | 5         |



## What Gets Automatically Created When EKS Is Created?

### Control Plane Components (AWS Managed)

AWS automatically manages:
    Kubernetes API Server
    etcd
    Controller Manager
    Scheduler

You cannot SSH into these servers.


